research_municipality_step.notes: Trenton, New Jersey, operates under a mayor-council system. The Mayor's term ends on December 31, 2026. The City Council consists of seven members; three are elected at-large, and four are elected by ward. The terms for at-large council members end on January 1, 2027, and for ward council members on January 1, 2029. Crystal Feliciano was voted Council President and Jenna Figueroa Kettenburg as Council Vice President on January 4, 2024.
